+The revised code uses, by default, a time-direction density-compatible integrating-factor update.  Let
+\begin{equation}\label{eq:q_factor_new}
+    E_k^n=\exp(u_k^n/\varepsilon),
+    \qquad
+    q_k^{n+1}=\frac{E_k^n}{E_k^{n+1}}
+    =\exp\left(\frac{u_k^n-u_k^{n+1}}{\varepsilon}\right).
+\end{equation}
+The fully discrete amplitude equation is then written as
+\begin{equation}\label{eq:fully_dc_if_new}
+\begin{aligned}
+    &\varepsilon\frac{W_{j,k}^{n+1}-q_k^{n+1}W_{j,k}^n}{\tau_n}
+    -D_k\delta_x^2W_{j,k}^{n+1}
+    -\varepsilon^2(E_k^{n+1})^{-1}
+      \delta_\theta^2\bigl(W_{j,\cdot}^{n+1}E_{\cdot}^{n+1}\bigr)_k  \\
+    &\qquad = (K_j-\rho_j^n)W_{j,k}^{n+1}.
+\end{aligned}
+\end{equation}
+Multiplying \eqref{eq:fully_dc_if_new} by \(E_k^{n+1}\) gives exactly the density-level update
+\begin{equation}\label{eq:density_level_if_new}
+    \varepsilon\frac{n_{j,k}^{n+1}-n_{j,k}^n}{\tau_n}
+    -D_k\delta_x^2n_{j,k}^{n+1}
+    -\varepsilon^2\delta_\theta^2n_{j,k}^{n+1}
+    =(K_j-\rho_j^n)n_{j,k}^{n+1}.
+\end{equation}
+Thus the terms involving \(H^n\), \(\widehat H\), and \(\delta_\theta^2u^{n+1}\) are no longer separately approximated in the amplitude equation; their contribution is absorbed by the factor \(q_k^{n+1}\).  This removes the time-discrete WKB chain-rule defect that appears when \(u\) and \(W\) are advanced independently.
+
+To improve positivity with respect to the density reaction, the revised code also provides the Patankar production--destruction form.  With
+\[
+    r_j^n=K_j-\rho_j^n,
+    \qquad
+    (r_j^n)_+=\max(r_j^n,0),
+    \qquad
+    (r_j^n)_-=\max(-r_j^n,0),
+\]
+\eqref{eq:density_level_if_new} is replaced by
+\begin{equation}\label{eq:density_patankar_new}
+    \varepsilon\frac{n_{j,k}^{n+1}-n_{j,k}^n}{\tau_n}
+    -D_k\delta_x^2n_{j,k}^{n+1}
+    -\varepsilon^2\delta_\theta^2n_{j,k}^{n+1}
+    =(r_j^n)_+n_{j,k}^n-(r_j^n)_-n_{j,k}^{n+1}.
+\end{equation}
+Equivalently, in the WKB amplitude variable,
+\begin{equation}\label{eq:w_patankar_new}
+\begin{aligned}
+    &\varepsilon\frac{W_{j,k}^{n+1}-q_k^{n+1}W_{j,k}^n}{\tau_n}
+    -D_k\delta_x^2W_{j,k}^{n+1}
+    -\varepsilon^2(E_k^{n+1})^{-1}
+      \delta_\theta^2\bigl(W_{j,\cdot}^{n+1}E_{\cdot}^{n+1}\bigr)_k \\
+    &\qquad=(r_j^n)_+q_k^{n+1}W_{j,k}^n-(r_j^n)_-W_{j,k}^{n+1}.
+\end{aligned}
+\end{equation}
+This is the default reaction option in the revised code; setting the reaction option to ``implicit'' recovers \eqref{eq:fully_dc_if_new}.}
